Single.Single: If the output is OFF and RemainingTime is 0 seconds, move the PT (PresetTime) into the RemainingTime variable.

If the input is ON, and the output is OFF: On the rising edge move the RemainingTime into the PresetTime of the Timer. On the falling edge subtract the Timer ElapsedTime from the Timer PresetTime and store it as RemainingTime. Also, add the CurrentTime to the Timer ElapsedTime and store it as the CurrentTime. Allow the Timer to run, and if it completes, set the output to ON. Continuously add the CurrentTime to Timer ElapsedTime and update the RTON ElapsedTime.
